# UI-UX Component Prompt Builder - Cursor Rules

## 1. Project Architecture

### 1.1 Directory Structure Principles
```
ui-ux-component/
├── steps/                  # Step components for each wizard step
├── store/                  # Zustand state management
├── types/                  # TypeScript interfaces
└── utils/                  # Dictionary and markdown generator
```

### 1.2 File Naming Conventions
| Type | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| Components | PascalCase | `ComponentTypeStep.tsx` |
| Hooks | camelCase with `use` prefix | `useWizardNavigation.ts` |
| Utils | camelCase | `dictionary.ts` |
| Store | `use` prefix + Store suffix | `useWizardStore.ts` |
| Types | PascalCase | `WizardStep.ts` |
| Constants | SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE | `WIZARD_STEPS.ts` |

---

## 2. TypeScript Clean Code Standards

### 2.1 Type Definitions (STRICT MODE)
```typescript
function generatePrompt(state: WizardState): string

interface WizardState {
  currentStep: number;
  selections: WizardSelections;
}

type StepType = 
  | { kind: 'single'; options: SingleChoiceOption[] }
  | { kind: 'multiple'; options: MultipleChoiceOption[] }
```

### 2.2 Import Order
1. Next.js/React core imports
2. Third-party libraries (Zustand, Lucide)
3. Shadcn/Radix UI components
4. Custom components
5. Utils/Hooks/Store
6. Types

---

## 3. State Management Guidelines

### 3.1 Zustand Store Structure
```typescript
interface WizardStore {
  currentStep: number;
  setCurrentStep: (step: number) => void;
  nextStep: () => void;
  prevStep: () => void;
  selections: WizardSelections;
  updateSelection: (step: keyof WizardSelections, value: any) => void;
  generatedPrompt: string;
  generatePrompt: () => void;
  resetWizard: () => void;
}
```

### 3.2 State Update Rules
- Immutability First: Never mutate state directly
- Atomic Updates: Use spread operators for partial updates
- Type Safety: All updates must preserve TypeScript types
- No Side Effects in Store: Pure state management only

---

## 4. Component Architecture

### 4.1 Selectable Card Contract
```typescript
interface SelectableCardProps {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  description: string;
  icon: LucideIcon;
  selected: boolean;
  onSelect: (id: string) => void;
  mode: 'single' | 'multiple';
  optionalText?: string;
  onOptionalTextChange?: (text: string) => void;
}
```

### 4.2 Component Hierarchy
```
WizardShell
├── Header
│   └── Stepper (1-5 indicators)
├── StepContent
│   ├── ComponentTypeStep
│   ├── VibeStyleStep
│   ├── ColorSchemeStep
│   ├── InteractivityStep
│   └── OutputStep
└── Footer
    ├── BackButton
    └── NextButton
```

---

## 5. Markdown Generator Rules

### 5.1 Template Literal Structure
- Use tagged template literals for readability
- All selections MUST reference utils/dictionary.ts
- Include conditional rendering for optional fields
- Output must be valid Markdown

### 5.2 Dictionary Lookup Pattern
```typescript
const styleInstructions = dictionary.vibeStyles[selection.vibeStyle];
```

---

## 6. Performance Considerations

### 6.1 React Optimization
- Use useCallback for event handlers
- Use useMemo for expensive dictionary lookups
- Lazy load step components with dynamic() import

### 6.2 Bundle Optimization
- Shadcn components: import only what is needed
- Lucide icons: tree-shakeable named imports

---

## 7. Git and Commit Conventions

### 7.1 Branch Naming
- feature/ui-ux-component-step-{N}
- fix/ui-ux-selection-bug

### 7.2 Commit Messages
```
feat: add component type selection step
fix: resolve color scheme navigation issue
docs: update ui-ux architecture diagram
```
